Log-Log4perl-Layout-PatternLayout-Elapsed
=========================================

This layout is a subclass of Log::Log4perl::Layout::PatternLayout which adds the
format %R. This format is used to display the time elapsed between two
consecutive log events. This is new field is tracked by appender which means
that the times are accurate and independent.

NOTE: Log::Log4perl 1.25 includes already this functionality in
Log::Log4perl::Layout::PatternLayout. It's suggested that you upgrade your
version of Log::Log4perl. This module exists in the case where upgrading is not
an option.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

	Log::Log4perl
	Time::HiRes (optional)

